title: Penfield Boys Soccer Picks Up Huge Draw Versus Mighty Webster Schroeder on Senior Night
text:
Penfield Boys Soccer Picks Up Huge Draw Versus Mighty Webster Schroeder on Senior Night 
Updated: Tuesday, October 13 2015, 11:51 PM EDT 
Webster Schroeder boys soccer is firmly in the conversation of which team is the best in New York State this season across all classes, but allowed Penfield on their Senior Night to equalize in the second half - and eventually draw - despite a goal by Ryan Delaney with three minutes left in the first half. Leading up to Delaney's goal, Trevor Carney got a loose ball and sent what seemed initially like a shot attempt far post from way outside. Delaney came out of nowhere and slid forward to poke it home right before the opposing keeper plowed into him trying to save the attempt.
